(firstQuint)The Effect of Resistant Starch Bagels on Risk Factors of Type 2 Diabetes and Colorectal Cancer.

 Using a randomized, double-blind crossover study design, we will determine the effect of consuming bagels made with resistant starch daily for 8-weeks can reduce the risk of type 2 diabetes and colon cancer in an adults who are at an increased risk for type 2 diabetes.

 Additionally, we will compare the satiating effect of these bagels to that of a standard bagel.

